  "instructions": [
    "preheat the air fryer to 400°f (200°c).",
    "line the air fryer basket with a liner and add the chopped onion, sweet potatoes, bell peppers, and carrots. Toss with 1 tbsp of coconut oil and cook for 15 minutes, shaking halfway through.",
    "in a large bowl, mix together the chickpeas, turmeric, garam masala, salt, and black pepper.",
    "add the cooked sweet potato mixture to the chickpea mixture and toss to combine.",
    "cook in the air fryer at 400°f (200°c) for an additional 10 minutes, shaking halfway through.",
    "add the chopped scallions and lemon juice to the bowl and toss to combine.",
    "fluff the cooked turmeric rice with a fork and divide among four bowls.",
    "top each bowl with the charred sweet potato mixture and serve immediately."
  ],
